Here is the cleaned up text:

Set up your enhanced bot to request and store a file upload from a customer, reducing agent handle time by collecting files before an agent joins the conversation. For example, request documentation related to an insurance or other reimbursement claim.

To use this feature, you need Einstein Bots available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience. Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Required user permissions:

* Customize Application
* Modify Metadata
* Manage Bots

Supported file types and sizes vary by channel.

To create a File dialog step:

1. From the Bot Builder, select Dialogs.
2. Select the dialog that you want to use to receive a file upload.
3. Drag the File dialog step onto the canvas.
4. In the Step Properties panel, in the File Interaction field, select Receive File.
5. Enter a message that prompts the bot end user to send a file.
6. Select or create an ID list variable with the object type set to Content Version to store the reference to the file.

When a file upload is successful, the file is attached to the messaging session and stored in the Files page of Setup.

Save your changes and activate your bot.
title: Enhanced Bots for File Upload
